{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:57:44.624Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"5g85nu46","input":{"summary":"I reviewed and verified the Pydantic schemas created for the portal and admin APIs in the GFF AI local MVP backend platform.\n\n### Files Changed/Created:\n- `backend/app/schemas/user.py` (Modified to support `UserUpdate`, expanded `UserResponse` fields to fully align with Database models and UI expectations, added ORM compatibility via `from_attributes = True`)\n- `backend/app/schemas/__init__.py` (Modified to import and expose all client, project, agent, document, invoice, support, governance, and auth schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/auth.py` (Created LoginRequest, TokenResponse, and CurrentUserResponse Pydantic schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/client_account.py` (Created ClientAccount schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/project.py` (Created Project schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/agent_operation.py` (Created AgentOperation schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/document_item.py` (Created DocumentItem schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/invoice.py` (Created Invoice schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/support_ticket.py` (Created SupportTicket schemas)\n- `backend/app/schemas/governance_item.py` (Created GovernanceItem schemas)\n\n### Summary of Implementation:\n- Each model is fully mapped to corresponding Base, Create, Update, and Response Pydantic v2 schemas.\n- High-fidelity type definitions perfectly match database constraints and handle optional/nullable fields correctly.\n- Enabled `from_attributes = True` for all Response models to support clean integration with SQLAlchemy ORM models.\n- Avoided exposing sensitive database credentials or password hashes in Response objects.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Wrote and executed a Python schema integration test suite (`backend/test_schemas_instantiation.py`) which imports every schema class, instantiates them with realistic mock payload data, and executes standard validation on mock database instances (using `model_validate`).\n- The test output reported `Success: All Pydantic schemas created and validated successfully!`.\n- Ran `git status` and confirmed only the expected schema files were affected.\n\n### Limitations:\n- The backend setup serves as a local MVP platform without live OAuth servers/complex infrastructure integrations, completely adhering to gff-ai-guardrails constraints.","verified":true}}}
